        <div n="399-700B" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-399-700B-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-399-700B-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-399-700B-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-399-700B-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-399-700B-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-399-700B-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-399-700B-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-399-700B-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-399-700B-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-399-700B-line-1"> As Clever Tom Clinch while the Rabble were bawling&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-399-700B-line-2"> Rode stately through Holbourn to die in his Calling</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-399-700B-line-3"> He Stopt at the George for a Bottle of sack</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-399-700B-line-4"> And promised to pay for it when he came back</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-399-700B-line-5"> His Waistcoat &amp; Stockings &amp; Breeches were White</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-399-700B-line-6"> His Cap had a new Cherry Ribbon to tye<hi rend="sup">ṭ</hi></l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-399-700B-line-7"> The Maids to the Doors &amp; the Balconies ran</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-399-700B-line-8"> And said Lack·a·day he·s a proper young Man</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-399-700B-line-9"> But as from the Windows the Ladies he spy<hi rend="sup">ḍ</hi></l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-399-700B-line-10"> Like a Beau in the Box he bow<hi rend="sup">d</hi> low on each side</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-399-700B-line-11"> And when his last Speech the loud Hawkers did cry</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-399-700B-line-12"> He swore from his Cart it was all a d──d Lie</l><l n="13" xml:id="spp-399-700B-line-13"> The Hangman for pardon fell down on his Knee</l><l n="14" xml:id="spp-399-700B-line-14"> Tom gave him a kick in the Guts for his Fee</l><l n="15" xml:id="spp-399-700B-line-15"> Then said I must speak to the People a little</l><l n="16" xml:id="spp-399-700B-line-16"> But I'll see you all d──d before I will whittle<ref target="#spp-399-700B-footnote-1">1</ref><note place="foot" n="1" xml:id="spp-399-700B-footnote-1">Whittle a Cant word for confessing at the Gallows</note></l><l n="17" xml:id="spp-399-700B-line-17"> My honest Friend Wild may he long hold his Place</l><l n="18" xml:id="spp-399-700B-line-18"> He lengthen<hi rend="sup">d</hi> my Life with a whole Year of grace</l><l n="19" xml:id="spp-399-700B-line-19"> Take Courage Dear Comrades &amp; be not afraid</l><l n="20" xml:id="spp-399-700B-line-20"> Nor Slip this occasion to follow your trade</l><l n="21" xml:id="spp-399-700B-line-21"> My Concience is Clear &amp; my Spirits are Calm</l><l n="22" xml:id="spp-399-700B-line-22"> And thus I go of without Prayer·Book or psalm</l><l n="23" xml:id="spp-399-700B-line-23"> Then follow the Practice of Clever Tom Clinch</l><l n="24" xml:id="spp-399-700B-line-24"> Who hung like a Hero &amp; never would flinch399-700B   </l></lg></div>
